    <string name="modifiers_selectors_hint">
## Choose how to generate your ability modifiers

Choose based on your preferred level of customization, speed of character creation, and campaign style.

### • Point Buy
Allocate a fixed pool of points (typically **27**) to spend on Strength, Dexterity, Constitution, Intelligence, Wisdom, and Charisma.
This method ensures balanced characters of roughly equal power and is ideal for long-term campaigns where optimization and fairness matter.

### • Standard Array
Use the preset scores *[15, 14, 13, 12, 10, 8]* and assign them to your abilities as you like.
This approach speeds up creation — perfect for one-shots, convention games, or groups new to the rules — while still offering meaningful choice.

### • Manual Entry
Enter any combination of values you and your DM agree on, whether from a homebrew system, a special event, or a thematic build.
This gives maximum flexibility for narrative experiments, high-power campaigns, or strictly role-play-driven characters.

---

Use **Point Buy** when you want balanced power and optimization, **Standard Array** for quick, fair setup, and **Manual Entry** to push creative or story-driven boundaries.
